Among the best Bible apps I've used, ranking up there with Sword. Very clean interface. Affordable.   Many content options to choose from.   I, personally, have it with Strongs Concordance, the Study Bible, and the Matthew Henry Commentary. I have all those resources in books, but it's nice to be able to access each of those resources at the touch of a button, instead of having to go grab my Matt Henry Bible, flip to the page, etc.  It's all easily accessible.  My only qualm, and would love to see this added, or at least added as an option the user can toggle: There is a SINGLE tab at the bottom for your content.  In my case, the study bible notes by default.  I can change that tab to take me to my Matt Henry commentary if I want, but I can't have both. So if I read study bible notes and want to see what Matt Henry's thoughts are, I have to goto settings and change it.  Then if I want to see my study bible notes, I have to go back to settings and change it back.  Seems unnecessary and tedious. I'd like the option to have 2 (or more) tabs, so I can access either at the touch of a tab, without having to goto settings each time.

This app let's you click and see the Greek and Hebrew defined meaning right 
on the verse using a concordance dictionary. It also let you look up the 
definition in the language of today which is sometimes a completely 
different meaning. So that helps me to be able to rightly understand what 
the true meaning of the words are saying because it's not the same today. 
So I get a more accurate information on what I am reading and that gives 
the true knowledge and understanding of the message of the time it was 
written. It also pulls up all the cross reference verses so I can read them 
to get a better understanding of the scripture. I can also save the verse, 
make notes on the verse and highlight. I just love this app. Last it has 
daily verses and devotionals that I can read to start my day in the word 
God! Thank you for making everything I needed to be able to study correctly 
and accurately! To be able to rightly divide the Word of God!
